  "conclusion": "For c4 full-native/no-chunk decode, forcing full-attention context replay to per-row is the first tested single-stage diagnostic that restores generated-token equality: both context+gate per_row and context_only per_row are green [137,137,137,137]. Post-attention-only, O-output-only, gate-only, KV-append-only, and MoE-only variants stay red, so the c4 retained blocker is isolated to the native batched context path rather than late O/post/MoE. The same context replay does not fully fix c8, which remains red on rows 4..6; c8 likely has an additional row-count/chunking interaction. No throughput claim is made.",
